<font face="arial,helvetica" color="006633" size="4"><b>OUR MISSION:����&nbsp;</b></font>
<!-- #### SEC0 body #### -->
<font face="arial,helvetica" color="006633" size="3"><p>TO PRESERVE SUFFIELD&#039;S ENVIRONMENT THROUGH ACQUISITION AND MAINTENANCE OF ECOLOGICALLY SIGNIFICANT UNDEVELOPED LAND LOCATED IN SUFFIELD AND WEST SUFFIELD CONNECTICUT.
<p>TO KEEP THE NATURAL BEAUTY OF OUR FARMLANDS, WOODLANDS, AND WETLANDS FOR FUTURE GENERATIONS.</td></tr>
<tr valign="top"><td valign="top">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr>
<!-- #### LEAD #### -->
<td colspan="3" align="left" valign="top"><font face="arial,helvetica" color="006633" size="4"><b>LAND CONSERVANCY NEWS ADD EVENTS</b></font>&nbsp;
<!-- #### SEC2 body #### -->
<font face="arial,helvetica" color="006633" size="3"><p><p><b><font color="red">Connecticut Trails Day</b></font><p>

The 15th annual Trails Day, sponsored by Connecticut Forest and Parks Association, will be celebrated on Saturday and Sunday, June 2-3, 2007 with a variety of hiking opportunities across Connecticut.  In Suffield, there will be a hike on Saturday, June 2 along the Metacomet Trail heading several miles south from Mountain Road to the town line and back through Suffield Land Conservancy and Sunrise Park lands. This hike will start at 10 am with an easy pace over hilly terrain.  Assuming good visibility, excellent views from the trap rock ridge include Manitook Mountain, the Heublein Tower, and the Litchfield hills.  Hawks and vultures can often be seen cruising in the air currents along the ridge and a few woodland wildflowers may still be found.  Everyone is welcome.

Those interested in the hike should meet on Mountain Road at the Alcorn properties near the intersection with Phelps Road and should bring water, lunch, sunscreen, and insect repellent as desired.  Comfortable sturdy shoes or hiking boots and socks should be worn.  Rain will cancel the hike. For further information, contact hike leader, Mike Stanley, at 668-5304. or lstangardn@aol.com<p><p><b><font color="red">Property Maintenance</b></font><p>



It is springtime again and time to clean up some of our properties so they can be enjoyed by hikers, birders, and others interested in the outdoors.  This year we will focus on cleaning up the Austin Brook trail which runs from Sunrise Park into Suffield Land Conservancy�s Spencer Preserve.  We will meet at 9 am on June 9 at the Sunrise Park pavilion and walk the trail into the conservancy property, finishing up by noon.  We will be mostly  trimming brush, so bring pruners, gloves, sturdy shoes, and water.  

 The event will be cancelled if we have bad weather.  For Additional information or questions, call Mike Stanley at 668-5304  or email  lstangardn@aol.com


</td></tr>
